article.description: — Terri Miller Jr.'s 17 points helped Louisiana Tech defeat Jacksonville State 63-58 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Miller sparks Louisiana Tech to 63-58 victory over Jacksonville State
article.linkText: Miller sparks Louisiana Tech to 63-58 victory over Jacksonville State
article.story: RUSTON, La. -- — Terri Miller Jr.'s 17 points helped Louisiana Tech defeat Jacksonville State 63-58 on Thursday night. Miller shot 7 of 9 from the field and 3 for 5 from the line for the Bulldogs (17-8, 7-3 Conference USA). Tahlik Chavez and Isaiah Crawford both scored 13 with Chavez adding five rebounds. Juwan Perdue led the Gamecocks (12-14, 4-7) with 11 points and six rebounds. Ivan Reynolds added 10 points and Travis Roberts scored nine. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
